<Link id="l01205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1205"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This function is used to enforce the topological node id property</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1206"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// leveraged during instruction selection. Before the selection process all</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1207"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// nodes are given a non-negative id such that all nodes have a greater id than</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1208"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// their operands. As this holds transitively we can prune checks that a node N</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1209"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// is a predecessor of M another by not recursively checking through M&#39;s</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1210"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// operands if N&#39;s ID is larger than M&#39;s ID. This significantly improves</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1211"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// performance of various legality checks (e.g. IsLegalToFold / UpdateChains).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1212"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1213"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// However, when we fuse multiple nodes into a single node during the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1214"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// selection we may induce a predecessor relationship between inputs and</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1215"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// outputs of distinct nodes being merged, violating the topological property.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01216" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1216"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Should a fused node have a successor which has yet to be selected,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1217"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// our legality checks would be incorrect. To avoid this we mark all unselected</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1218"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// successor nodes, i.e. id != -1, as invalid for pruning by bit-negating (x =&gt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01219" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1219"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// (-(x+1))) the ids and modify our pruning check to ignore negative Ids of M.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01220" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1220"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We use bit-negation to more clearly enforce that node id -1 can only be</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01221" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1221"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// achieved by selected nodes. As the conversion is reversable to the original</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01222" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1222"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Id, topological pruning can still be leveraged when looking for unselected</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01223" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1223"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// nodes. This method is called internally in all ISel replacement related</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01224" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1224"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// functions.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01225" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1225" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/selectiondagisel/#a6d548a27495e0e978c1ef0cc0f185744"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/selectiondagisel/#a6d548a27495e0e978c1ef0cc0f185744">SelectionDAGISel::EnforceNodeIdInvariant</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdnode">SDNode</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/classes/node">Node</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2391"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If Root use can somehow reach N through a path that doesn&#39;t contain</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2392"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// U then folding N would create a cycle. e.g. In the following</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2393"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// diagram, Root can reach N through X. If N is folded into Root, then</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2394"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// X is both a predecessor and a successor of U.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2395"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02396" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2396"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//          &#91;N&#42;&#93;           //</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2402"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//          \\ /            //</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2403"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//         &#91;Root&#42;&#93;         //</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2404"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2405"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &#42; indicates nodes to be folded together.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2406"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2407"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If Root produces glue, then it gets (even more) interesting. Since it</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2408"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// will be &quot;glued&quot; together with its glue use in the scheduler, we need to</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2409"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// check if it might reach N.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2410"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2411"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//          &#91;N&#42;&#93;           //</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2417"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//          \\      |       //</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02424" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2424"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//           f  /          //</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02425" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2425"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//           | /           //</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02426" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2426"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//          &#91;GU&#93;           //</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02427" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2427"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02428" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2428"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If GU (glue use) indirectly reaches N (the load), and Root folds N</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02429" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2429"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// (call it Fold), then X is a predecessor of GU and a successor of</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02430" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2430"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Fold. But since Fold and GU are glued together, this will create</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02438" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2438"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (!GU)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02439" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2439"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">break</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02440" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2440"><Highlight kind="normal">    Root = GU;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02441" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2441"><Highlight kind="normal">    VT = Root-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdnode/#ac0a534d63ac5c5b87f36acdade953fbe">getValueType</a>(Root-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdnode/#a7f06dbaee5fa2b239de548d0a775b25b">getNumValues</a>()-1);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02442" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2442"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02443" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2443"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If our query node has a glue result with a use, we&#39;ve walked up it.  If</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02444" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2444"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the user (which has already been selected) has a chain or indirectly uses</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02449" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2449"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02450" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2450"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> !<a href="#a7e5a9b5c5f87a0f7d2227881e84be8a2">findNonImmUse</a>(Root, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/regcomp-c/#a0240ac851181b84ac374872dc5434ee4">N</a>.getNode(), U, IgnoreChains);</Highlight></CodeLine>
